This is by far one of my most favorite games. I love the social aspect of the game, where you can donate troops, fight a war together, and participate in clan games. I've met many people, we run a clan family of over 100 people and it's fun to socialize. I also like how it's not pay to win, you can play and not buy anything and do just fine. CWL is fun, Clan games is fun, Builder Hall could be more fun. Maybe add wars to that, or donation troops. The game is also pretty balanced, nothing too OP.

Many updates that take up TONS of storage. Other than that, fun game of strategy, and team work. But don't rely to much on your clan mates as people have lives and get busy, where others are children who don't know any better. Been playing this game for around 6 years now. Don't waste your money on packages, you will get there in time.

Love this game. Been playing it for years, I quit for 2 years because I lost my old account, recently came back to see Supercell removed global chat? Awful idea, and marketing tactic, global chat connected many players from all around the world, and kept people playing because they can talk with other clashers, and lovers of the company. My one wish for this game is that Supercell brings back global chat.

So kids like me cant get access to all the unique features that only youtubers buy. And the pricing of magic items in the game is to irreasonable too. These are my queries. Please fix it SUPERCELL!

An original game that is best with friends, give a promotion to whoever made the music. Love this game. Started playing on December 2015 up to this day (review day). All the units and buildings in this game are well-balanced, updates to updates. The reason I gave this 4 stars instead of 5 was because they removed one of the biggest and coolest feature in the game which was Global Chat. Also, the game support team sometimes aren't that great or kind enough to help, you'll probably just get bot messages. Other than that everything is good.

The idea of the game is the thing I love about this game. A few things i'd like is to have laboratory upgrades take less time. clash of clans is a nice game, but i think it can vastly be improved for instance, it would be nice to be able to donate gold and elixir to your clan mates perhaps it can be in accordance to the clan level, so that every time the clan level increases, the limit on the amount also increases, and the messaging can also be improved, because when i want to send a clan message to one person so that he can attack in war, well it just sends to every one on the clan lol oh yes it would also be nice to see who's online cause some people don't chat, so i don't know who's online ... Don't believe the hype: this is definitely not pay to win. I haven't spent a dime on the game and I feel like progression is fair. I Like this game because it will make you really plan what troops and spells you should choose and where to place them in the battlefield. But what I don't like is that when you don't get a perfect 3 stars, the deducted trophies is too many. I really enjoyed playing this game for a while. My daughter loves to spend the stars and choose things for the garden. Kind of a fun time waster. But I have noticed that the number of moves allotted for many of the levels has been reduced. For instance, I am on level 1633 right now. You have to get 22 mystery bags and drop 2 drinks to the bottom. Walk through videos show there used to be 30 moves. I only have 24 moves to start. It's pretty much impossible unless you have boosters.

I really like the game but it's really unfair. Ever since I updated the game yesterday it's been glitching. It doesn't want me to win this level I'm on. Every time I win it exits and I have to start over. And I only have 2 more chocolate decorations and I can't even buy them because it doesn't want me to. And all my decorations have just turned...invisible or something. Chocolate day is almost over and I can't do anything at all. I'm really frustrated and I feel like deleting the game now. HELP

Love all of the scapes games, they calm me down when I am upset, the give me something to do when I'm bored, & I also really like the way the game interacts with the players. I have been going through a lot lately. I had two deaths in my family & it affected me real bad. But when I play this game, it helps me get through all my bad days. Thank u so much for making these scapes game & if possible could more be made? Thanks again!

I download the game due to false advertising. I don't mind decorating the land. I get really aggravated with all the unnecessary things you have to do for example feed the dog, call someone, change the tire. I just want to make the property look nice without the stupid stuff. I also feel like $900 is to much for 3 extra moves when you only earn $70 when you win a level. I actually go a long time without playing because some of the levels are very hard.

I've had this game for a while and I enjoy it, I like the puzzles and enjoy upgrading the garden. However, the reason I'm only rating it 2 stars is because I've seen a lot of ads lately that are nothing like the actual game. The puzzles are similar to Candy Crush. That's fine with me, I like those, but the false advertising gets on my nerves.

Love playing this game but have one issue. The events are pretty impossible to complete or even get close to completing (finishing rooms or accumulating decorations). I played a lot more than I usually do during this most recent chocolate event and could not accumulate enough points fast enough. Decorations should cost less and it would be much more rewarding to play more.

Last update has ruined it. Since the last update the game freezes and exits (not while in the garden screens, only during gameplay). If you've used boosters (either won, paid for or first attempt lightening) you can kiss them goodbye. If it crashes out just as you complete the stage, this is also lost so you have to redo it (bearing in mind any boosters you used, or started with, are lost). Irrititating to the point of making the game unplayable.

I updated this game on June 30th and since then, like others, the game has become increasingly slow to load, my points seem to be lower than usual and all of the boosters glitch and freeze. I'm on level 1832 and I'd hate to uninstall after playing daily, but this is absolutely frustrating. Please get us an update soon. Thanks!

First I will say that I like the game however after playing it , I have started to hate it as well. The reason I tried this game is the misleading ad that showed the mini game, there was only three, also, since the last update the game is virtually impossible to play, glitching, freezing and extremely slow to load and play. Also, I am not impressed with the cost of playing this game, there is very little payback for winning and completing levels.

I'm having the same problems as Janice Angel and Takeema Johnson. I also got in touch with game makers as I had 12 moves left and only 4 butterflies to catch. Should have been a piece of cake but not a single butterfly appeared. The game makers don't care. Also it's gotten real sluggish and you need a lot more stars to be able to do something on your list at the new garden site. I also never completed a single room to renovate, :(. It's become very frustrating to play which is a shame.

I can't get out in my gardens much anymore so this game helps me to still work in a garden. I've been playing almost 3yrs. I'm not tired of it yet. It's my favorite. I am having problems with it shutting down and slow motion moves. It did updated but still slow motion and shuts down. : ( now it says to update again but my phone has very little storage left. I'm so disappointed.

Enjoy the game but the last few updates have made it super glitchy, each time I finish a level I get a black screen and have to re-start the game multiple times before it works again. Please fix this as it is super annoying especially when you have 30mins of free lives and you spend the whole time trying to get the game working!

I like this game so much, thanks for putting the effort into it! It was fun and encouraging initially but when I noticed that the game was sort of like "cheating", my interest faded. 1. When I expected the fireworks to target the elements I need, they purposely missed the elements on the last step; 2. the butterflies are nowhere to be seen; 3. the number of exploding of power-ups to get rainbow blast is inconsistent. Sometimes I need 3-4 explodes, sometimes up to 10 to get the rainbow charged.

Support was no help at all. To Dean Whiteley, actually - it gets much worse. Don't spend your money. Also, the more coins and boosters you buy, the more the game takes or cheats you out of your purchases. You end up losing much more. Fun at first. I played for almost a year. Trust me. It cheats you out of more and more money. Besides the game cheating people, don't count on getting proper support.

500 levels and above the boards are absolutely ridiculous. Not enough moves to complete them w/o boosters. Not enough specific items on the board (butterflies, apples, etc.). By the time they fall, you're out of movesThe Parrot package was good, at first, but you won't win the grand prize unless you pay to pass each board. Even with the free time that is sometimes given, you waste most of it on the "ridiculous" boards. And lastly this is not the game that is advertised. Uninstalling @ level 691

As of the mid June update, the game now lags, and can take longer to load than before. Plus they added some unnecessary annoying sounds to the ones they already had. Poorly executed. The levels get more difficult as you go, encouraging you to buy special skills to pass. But I think the shameful part is they encourage moves are not the best ones to make. You get the feeling they are encouraging you to waste a move so you don't pass which brings you to have to purchase the special skills to do so.

Has some interesting challenges in play. some levels are frustrating though. The rewards do seem a bit sparse given the difficulty of the levels. seems to me that certain harder levels should be worth more than 1 point. when it can take a week to defeat a really hard level, you actually feel cheated to only get one point. rewards seem a bit stingy to be honest at certain times. I wish there were additional ways to earn stars. Here's hoping that may happen.

It's wonderful game, But why it doesn't have night mood, All buildings are beautiful built, plus surrounded lights and lamps, so if u turn it on , it doesn't show the beauty of the city because it's already day light, So u can update the game and add night mood, so u can see the difference, plus if u add some more functions such as saving the picture of your builded city. one more request, When the player running out of moves and use Stars to complete, Give more than 5 moves at least 10+ Thanks

The mini games that have been advertised are not available when playing the game. I've reached level 1324 and only been able to play two mini games. The app also just uploaded and is running slow and glitches. Game is frustrating, you only have 5 lives and as it increases the normal levels seem more difficult than the "hard" or "super hard" levels. You need certain extras to pass and if you pay for them, you end up spending more money. The game is addictive and has fun elements.

This is a very fun game. You beat levels to earn stars and you need stars to complete tasks in the garden. I love the way your able to design parts of the garden. My only problem is the lives. If you don't beat a level you lose a life so then you have to wait 30mins for another life, you can maximum 5 lives at a time. I wouldn't mind them if it took less time to get a life or your lives are refilled after 30mins. Also, the new update is very glitchy. Otherwise it is a very fun game!

The game is fun and challenging to play, and the levels become incrementally more challenging so that it isn't boring, but also not impossible. Creating the garden world as you go in between plays is also kinda fun. However, I do wish the "renovation" bonus challenges did not have a time limit. Some of us have jobs to attend and kids to raise, we can't just power through a nonstop weekend of playing games on our phones! It would be nice to have those changed to level completion based.

Fun game but once you reach higher levels it takes weeks to pass and it gets boring. Now every second level is either hard or super hard. You do belong to teams and once you get to these levels over 3600+ your team carries you a bit, which is neither fair nor fun. I got rid of the sister game nearly a year ago for the same reason. I have had enough. Not coming back to this game.

I downloaded the game as I liked the mini games it showed. But you only get these occasionally and only for the first few levels which was disappointing . Later levels are difficult to complete without boosts which you generally have to pay for. So hence it taking me a long time to progress as I don't buy them. Nice pictures and quirky tales. So far no glitches.

I came because I thought this was something it is not. In the ad, it was a guess the right item to progress through the game. What it turned out to be is a very slow, glitchy, match 3 type game. I played through it a few times, and I could feel myself becoming physically angered by this game. You play through a million levels, which have very small rewards for solving the puzzles, and then eventually you get to a mini game, that is just 3 choices long, and the answers to it are just obvious.

Love the game! However, I wish they'll give more than one star per winning levels, especially on the harder levels, the winning stars should be more since most of the tasks requires 3 or more sometimes within each tasks. Switching teams is not as easy as the instructions says and is not fair that I can't chose to be on a team that works as hard as me to win since the requirements to join are levels that I haven't even reach just because I recently started the game

I downloaded this game originally because it was advertised as being a trap door puzzle type of game. I'm at level 1723 have yet to play a trap door puzzle game. My biggest pet peeve is that once you are into the higher levels, its nearly impossible to fully complete a room challenge even with the most recent upgrade. To date, I have only been able to complete one room and that was the very first room. Also, you lose everything you have bought with your room tickets which is a bummer.

Not what I wanted, It is just a candy crush wanna be. I do like the concept of playing a match to get stars and fix the place up. Its just I wanted minigames which they do have but are so few and so far that the game is not worth playing. I do not want to play a candy crush game. Its a shame as I really do think the game is ok, but I was lead on to believe it was something else. So for that I am Uninstalling this game.

I love the game, however feel that one star per level is not enough for the tasks that require more, especially when it's simple tasks that needs to be done. I also feel like more renovation tickets should be given per level as it is very hard renovating the entire room when each renovation requires so much tickets, which then means that you do not complete the room. What is even more unfair is when you earn eternal life, but are forced to play it then and there, and not on your own time!!

I really enjoy this game. But i have problem here. Since 3 weeks ago, when I play the game, it keep lagging. The game is running slow. That's make my phone hot. I have tried to reinstal several time, but it didn't work. The game still lagging. I don't know what's wrong. I hope you guys can fix the problem. My phone is xiaomi redmi note 8.

I think the game has a bug after the golden ticket season is completed. I cannot play, the Golden ticket window is popping up continuously on the screen, I cannot click it, close it or even buy the damn thing. I tried to unninstal, remove it from Facebook, the same thing happens. Please fix it or at least, if this is the end for users who do not spend real money on this game, inform us and move on. Update: so the bug was fixed, it's working now, but after the last update the game is s**t.

I'm giving it 2stars until it's fixed bc I'm not sure if there was a recent update or not, but I CAN'T HARDLY STAND to play it anymore. It laggs so bad that it acts like it's got a bad internet connection when it doesn't need it to work.  I like the game very much & I buy all the time on it for extra power ups. It's very frustrating that it worked just fine, smooth, seamless & fast about a week & a half ago.....but now, I'm about to just let it hang in limbo & stop playing it.

I love the garden but hate that it comes up with stupid stuff like fixing a jack of getting a kids helicopter off the roof and then I have to pay for it. I can't say 'no' to any of the gaudy junk they force me to include or change even when I like the way it was before they're update. I have to pay for everything they come up with before I can move on to the next garden.

I really enjoyed playing initially but the games got really hard, to the point that I lost about 15 lives in a row, and I don't know why you have to wait so long to get another life, it is frustrating and annoying, I even quit a few games part way through as I knew I wasn't going to complete it. I wanted a game that was fun and though challenging was achievable and I would rather pay for a game up front than be expected to pay money throughout just to move on a level.

The game was running smoothly until recently. Now its freezing and lagging to the point that I am about to uninstall it. I've spent money on this game and it is just not worth it. I would demand a refund if I knew I'd get my money I wasted on a game that freezes all the time! UPDATE: I'm uninstalling the game. I AM TIRED OF IT CRASHING!!! Do not waste your time on this game!

It nothing like the advertisement. It is mainly candy crush that gives you just 1 star per level and you need a lot of stars to progress with renovation of your garden. There are no choices. The tasks have to be done as preset in the game. Sometimes helping a passerby, keeping a dog and then feeding it even if you don't like dogs. The only choices are in the decoration items (types of trees and flowers, etc). The gardens look pretty after renovation. Download if you want to play candy crush.

One of the worst app. I don't know why they said save on Facebook. I had unlocked many levels and I was on 2000+ levels and was save with Facebook but now after change my mobile phone, I am not able to get my lost game. It starts from level 2 But when I open candy crush it open with my same level. Candy crush is much better than this game.

I got this game due to the advertisements which it FALSELY makes you think it's a puzzle game. These puzzles only happened maybe 5-6 times and I'm now on level 800+!!. This is SO misleading in your advertising! 98% of the tasks NOW require anywhere from 3 to 6 games to complete a single task! That is WAY too many tasks required to get anything done and it's getting very boring. Also, we used to be able to choose our garden designs. That only happens maybe 5% of the time. This is getting BORING!!

Great game. I love it!... Edit... Had to take a star off, cause every since I updated the game it won't stop freezing... And Why show mini games where we would have to help do whatever and it is not in the game? I have only done it like 3 times and thats it. Nice game but.. I am pretty sure thats what lead people to download the game. I really would love to see ans solve those puzzles please!

I absolutely love this game. I spend a fair amount of money, and am approaching level 3000. However, after this last update, my game has been EXTREMELY laggy amd crashes a lot. I have lost dozens of boosters and thousands of coins simply for no reason other than the game lags out and does what it wants. I'm losing levels that I have finished and losing win streaks as well. If this continues, I will be removing the game and forgetting it.

I have to agree with alot of the critical reviews on this game. Minimal ads is great however, any level past lvl 500 is near impossible. If I have managed to pass a level beyond 500 it was through sheer fluke. There are hardly any goes to do it in and I've spent days on the same level which becomes boring and frustrating rather than entertaining. I'm sure the reason is to prompt the player to spend money on boosters. Also I've only seen the mini game a handful of times. False advertising.

I love this game but it's becoming tedious now with just 5 lives and super tough levels to clear in one go. Earning stars and coins is super tough too! And it tells me to buy with real money, I won't do that!! I sometimes take days to clear one level. You should increase the lives or quantity of rewards. The game is fun but the feature is terribly annoying!

I am a bit disappointed with the team. Reasons are- 1. Advertisement is misleading. It shows a puzzle based game while delivery is a match- three sort of game. 2. Unnecessary task for people. If u don't want to give them a room, why make them design from the start. U need to play and earn points and then u wont ever be able to finish the task list to get a designed room. So all the efforts goes to waste. It's a suggestion to the team - think for some alternative to this.

I found this game to be a "bait and switch". It's nothing like the advertisements. Instead of the game of logic as advertised, it is a matching game of fruit and power bombs. Although the actual game play is fun, the premise is a set up to pay into the game, buying coins and power ups, to assist as the levels become harder. The game takes up loads of space on your phone, and eventually takes longer and longer to load as you continue to decorate the garden spaces. It's not what I expected

the level is getting more difficult, and I think the assistance provided is not enough, because I have to win continuously, come on this game was originally not as difficult as this, why does the hard level always appear at every level change, I'm so lazy to play it, because it's too difficult ,, and the last update , there is a very annoying sound, please return the previous version only ..

I love this game, it's so addictive, shame you have to pay for additional power ups and I can't buy them with "in game" money. I see you have made more chance to double up on renovation vouchers, but I still never get enough to complete a room!!! Sometimes less is more, I think sometimes there are too many items in one location which just makes it tacky and garish

At first I really liked this game. However I have spent well over $200 to keep it going. It is very addictive. When you run out of coins in order to win games to advance the garden you must purchase coins and other helpers for the game such as a shovel, rake, glove, bombs Etc. It is too expensive and that is why I don't play it much anymore. I am not rich and cannot afford this game. The makers of this game need to figure out a way to keep it going without having to keep making purchases.

I too have come to hate this game, although I really like the graphics, etc. But it is so slow loading and very sluggish. It also takes a lot of games to do a task, progress is frustrating and gets boring. And it's very hard to complete games without purchasing extra coins, etc.

The game is rigged and should be reported to goggle play, you have to spend money to proceed, every time you spend it let's you win games but not enough to win tournaments if you don't spend you got no chance, don't download unless you got plenty of money. Wouldn't give this game one star, games get boring because you get stuck for days. And by the way you have to give it at least one star to be able to leave a comment.

The game is fun but the ads are misleading. You only do the problem solving things maybe like 3 times before they just give up on it, which is frustrating because I really enjoyed it. Also when you get rooms to renovate, you don't even get to keep the room if you don't complete EVERY ITEM which is does not happen once the levels get really hard. It starts to become next to impossible to do almost anything after a while. You're set up to fail, and spending any money on it is pointless.

Not enough mini games. - Mini games advertising is what drawed me in!- I just realized I played this game last year and deleted it for the same reason. Seems like Negative Reviews are piling up. Fool me once shame on you. Fooled me twice. When is the developer going to listen to the reviews? Not sure.... I don't like leaving negative reviews. I do like being positive. I please ask for your prompt response. God bless you. Jesus Loves Yas.

Really fun. Goes on forever though. But awesome graphics and good story line. I wish they didn't make you waste so many stars for tiny tasks. There's also the side rooms. I really wish they would let you go back and complete unfinished rooms. Not only that, but the amount of tickets that you need to build the rooms is ridiculous! You have almost no chance of completing the room unless you play constantly (which isn't feasable - we DO have lives, you know).

Good, I'm glad you removed the waiting time for construction work to be completed kudos for that. Can we also add the option to just skip any interact happening between the characters beyond the balloon talk. I just want to play the game and see progress in the renovations don't care much for what they say or seeing how the renovation is done. Overall, I love the game and I'm enjoying it

Awesome game but this game is very money hungry! You take forever to get a chest and its peanuts. Should be better incentives to make you want to keep playing or to beat levels. I'm really thinking about quitting and I'm into 3000 levels already...spent way to much money on this game with no benefit really except me paying to play... besides the rewards suck! You bust your butt trying to get as far as you can to get the rewards and you pay way more then what you get back. Deleting!! Game sucks!!

I like the game overall, but it can get boring. I deleted it then reinstalled it when I saw the new minigames, but it turns out you can't play them whenever you want. Also, I like to keep things minimalistic and aesthetically pleasing, but there are limited options for the garden decor and it bothers me because there is too much going on and its overwhelming. Please make other ways to get stars because the puzzles get boring after a while.

I've been playing this game for a while and I've had enough. I'm stuck at this level for days played it at least 30 times already. This game only lets you win if it wants to otherwise you're stuck there like i am now and the advert is so misleading there is nothing in the ad that is in the game. Smh uninstallingüôÑ

My favourite game for passing some time. Love the story line and all the different characters! The pets were an awesome touch! Also when a level gets hard i often just put it down for a day or 2 then come back and beat it. Lots of great rewards! Been playing for 4 years on and off and finally decided you deserve a rating :). Thanks for never disappointing me guys!!! Great job!

Challenging, without a ton of ads, but room for improvement Once you get over the bait-and-switch (because the games in the ads almost never happen), this is a decently challenging match-3 game. The early levels are really easy if you play these games a lot, but they get progressively harder in the triple-digit levels. There's just enough variety of tasks and boards to keep you playing. I wish you could turn off the match suggestions -- they get distracting when you're planning out your moves.

At first I gave 5 star but sorry, i have to update my review again because i'm so pissed of lately bcs this game. Actually I really enjoy this game, it's even more fun than candy crush. But lately the game is getting annoying. Sometimes 30 minutes passed and I can't even complete 1 LEVEL!! If you think about it some levels can only be passed with a ‚Äúluck‚Äù Even to get coins per level only around 70 coins, but if you want to add lives you have to pay 900 coins. Does that make sense?

So I updated my OS to Android 10 thinking it will function better there but its still the same lagging overall. It's a fun game but I don't like that you have to play a level so many times sometimes just to pass that level & sometimes you get down to 1 or 2 pieces to win, your lives run out, or they make it impossible for you to beat a level and you have to play that same level like 20 times before you can finally win. Can be fun & sometimes can be redundant & exhausting. But I still like the game & the way it works, just some of those other things I mentioned I don't like.

I used to really enjoy this game a long time ago. It's been "updated" almost beyond recognition. It used to be a time management/hidden object game that wasn't overrun with ads or a pay to play game. I don't mind the matching games so much but they really do seem to eat up your lives quickly (and I've always been good, quick at games like this ü§î). I love this game. However....... Im getting frustrated with it since the last update. It has kicked me off three times in the middle of playing. Not only do I lose a heart but now I have to play the same level again that I was so close to beating the level finally. Anyone else having issues with this?

I would give it 5 stars but ever since I did the update about 2 weeks ago I have had nothing but constant freezing and crashing. I have lost MANY power ups and loves that I actually purchased with real money and feeling pretty ripped off at the moment. I have opened a ticket in the help area of the game and no one has responded. Not thrilled with their customer service. Spend money and they rip you off by having a faulty game the freezes and crashes.

Normally I love the game. I play it multiple times a day. But here recently I've been playing less and less Because I got 3 hrs unlimited lifes. With that I completed 50 levels and just let the run of the time run out. I never used my level stars to complete task but next morning I was down to 12 stars and I am having to redo the levels I have already done. On top of that after completing these levels again I am not receiving my stars. So I am stuck completing these levels again an nothing to do

Just about had enough. I used to play multiple times a day, but levels are taking far too long to pass for too few rewards. The biggest issues are matching pieces to get rainbow balls or whatever they are and only getting a rocket, and earning stars only for them to be missing the next time I play. Also there's never enough time to finish rooms, and we have to get sometimes 5 or 6 stars to add something completely unnecessary. About ready to uninstall.

I absolutely love this game.... Im over level 2000. Just wish it didnt cost so much for boosters, etc. I hardly ever use the money won to buy different things for the garden itself. Have over $40K.... it would be kool to have an option to use THAT money to buy boosters. I mean, we earned it by playing... why limit the option or ability to use it on boosters or lives, etc.

It's frustrating at times, either it doesn't give you the pieces you need or worse! There are levels that start with certain pieces you need to do first, but if you have the bonus boosters it messes it up so you have to wait until you lose your boosters to actually do the level. Maybe add a option so you can use boosters when you want.

I really enjoy playing Gardenscapes. It's challenging, fun and a great way to pass the time. I have kind of gotten addicted, in a way, to the game. Once I got started playing it, I started looking forward to it every day. It's always something new. There are certain parts of the game that I cringe when I see them come up because my skills haven't gotten where I need them to be but eventually I get through them. It definitely keeps you in a great state of mind.

The game is very addictive. I have played over 3,000 levels. Though some levels can be very difficult with no help except from purchasing coins or boosters. It is a pleasant game and a good way to relax. My issue though is in mixing the lives for learning pet tricks and the real game together. Your extra lives should be linked to both games to make it more and interesting.

Starts great! Then it starts costing stars to do insignificant tasks but the game starts fun. Then, it becomes nearly possible to win games without boosters. I pay to play my games but will not continue to play when I'm forced to pay to advance at all, especially when the game is less about gardening and more about making phone calls and greeting guests.

Fun but cheap instances keep happening. Paid a lot of money for this and that. The last 3 times I have just minimized the window/app (to answer a call or something), it takes away the powerups I chose to use from my bank (like normal) but when I go back into the game it's on the garden where I select to play, fulfill a task, etc. It doesn't start off where I left off in the middle of the game. Just takes my items and makes me start over. It's bogus!

My boosters disappeared for no reason. I had 2 bombs, 2 rainbow blasts, and 3 extra moves. I had used many coins and booster to maintain my no loss streak. I notified them, and they did not even bother to answer me.. Months later. This happened to me again. Again, my magic hat boosters were not restored. Let me be clear. The problem is not on my end. I know what I am doing. I suppose I should delete the game. Seems better

can't download update. Game times out when i have boosters. I slide toward one way and am reverted. These tactics keep me from winning. I love this game; But I've been fustrated lately. Sometimes the game glitches and steals my stars. Good game, but the points rewarded for each level is very very less, and then we do not even have more moves, for purchasing more moves at a hard level, the prices are too high..the challenges are good, but then they should be possible to achieve if you give sufficient number of moves at the hard levels specially, even there is no gift rewards so that user can make use of it in hard levels. He is stuck at a level if the moves are less and its hard to cover. Please take this as a feedback.

The game is well planned with levels, difficulties and goals for building garden. Initially, the game was working well. But, after the recent update, on June 18,2020, the app has become too slow. Especially the animation part while using blasters and rainbow blaster. It might be some kind of a bug or something. Please fix it soon or restore the previous version. I gave 1 star to grab the attention. Will change it as soon as the animation bug is changed.

Since the last updates the game is ruined. I usually listen to podcasts while I play, but now if I open the game with headphones in, for some reason it makes the sound of my podcast come out of the phone speakers even with the headphones plugged in (I have game music switched off) . The Gameplay is now glitchy and it lags and seems unresponsive. I don't know if I'll carry on playing, after getting to level 366.

I used to love this game. I'm well past level 3000, and now my stomach is usually in knots when I play. The algorithm works like this: even a basic level is impossible to pass, even with boosters. Then suddenly, on day 3, everything falls just right and you pass no problem. It's ridiculous. Those complaining that renovations are impossible to complete are totally correct. I've never been able to do it. Not enough rewards for accomplishments, and I've never seen a mini game. Uninstalling.

Great game very addictive, really enjoying this but since i downloaded the last update the pieces take ages to move and it takes a really long time to switch between the screens, its really slow now which it wasnt before, I actually thought it was my phone until i came on here and read a few other reviews, also the levels are quite hard now, i do wish it was just about rennovating the garden and not having to play games in order to do it.

Game is pure greed. I understand in app purchases is personal choice. However I expect not to have issues it is currently experiencing with it's freezing and as a consequence muddled speed and app kicking you out in the middle of the game. I am in communication with the customer services and hope to be able to rewrite this review depending on their final response to the issue.

Until you guys give more stars for the levels that's being played. Your ratings will be very low. I hate the simple fact that every similar game gives more stars and so forth and Gardenscapes only gives you one star and asks for 8 stars just to build up your garden. I also hate that I spent the money that did on this game and wish that I didn't at all.

userName: Kitchen Chronicles With Joe and Tee
content: I am on level 6351 so clearly I love playing the game. But for the past three weeks or so, there has been issues. One -the game has been lagging and getting stuck horribly. To the point where I can't even play it. Two - I have had to play the Golden Cup three times already. Additional levels stop and start, stop and start. When is that going to stop?

Some of the levels are much too hard, almost impossible to win especially when designing the rooms. It takes too many levels to beat to accomplish the decorating goal. Another thing, when you win free time, you should be able to play when you want. When you stop playing the time should stop ticking which would allow players to play at their leisure. There's been times where I've won 5 hours. I don't want to be forced to play for 5 straight hours. So I end up forfeiting valuable game time

I have been playing this game for over 2 years. After the last update in June it will no longer even open. When it did only two times it was so slow and froze up constantly. The room challenges are terrible as some of us work for a living and can't play the game constantly. I don't understand why challenges can't last longer. Unfortunately, I will be uninstalling.

The game was running smoothly but as soon as the update was installed it started lagging and the animations became jerky. Please rectify it as it is spoiling the experience. Now you want me to make a second update and I am sure it will further deteriorate the experience. It also takes a lot of time to load which is very irritating. I am using Samsung note 4.

Hello, I was playing the game where he racing on the bike and getting flowers and coins. To be clear, this game is aimed at players paying real money, it's a business for the developers. Having said that, you can progress without paying for extras, it just limits how long you can play, not a bad thing in its own right. The games are all basically similar I.e making rows and clearing things off the playing area. Four stars only as the logic mini games which feature highly in the advertising, are very few and far between.

I love this game, the only negative thing I have to say is that you don't get enough moves in a lot of the goals to complete them, especially the hard levels, but very fun game, being able to restore different areas and I like how Austen acknowledges you, the amount of moves in goals is the reason I gave 4 stars for the gameplay, but great game in general

. the wheel never lands on jackpot or double rewards. it is improving in regards to landing on items besides lighting. You lose all bonuses/ power up for failing 1 level vs candy crush where you lose one bonus/power up per failed level progressively.

Also, for the renovation of rooms, it's fun but the prices of things we have to get are crazy high most of the time. Too expensive yet we don't get that much ticket from the game.

At first I thought this game was fun but now I don't. You spend so much time collecting stars just to use them up on the dumbest things when you want to use them for fixing up the yard.
